Urge my colleagues to pass #GAP Act so we can strengthen equal pay laws & combat wage inequality
Proud to work with @SenCapito @senrobportman @SenatorBurr @SenDeanHeller on #GAP Act
After hearing fr stakeholders, we updated #GAP Act this week to protect salary transparency & employees’ right to discuss
#GAP Act prohibits retaliation against employees who discuss their pay & tells employers they can’t institute pay secrecy policies
#GAP Act is a sensible approach to update, clarify and strengthen these laws
Unfortunately, there are a patchwork of laws & differing court opinions tht govern employees’ ability to discuss pay w/o retaliation
#GAP Act makes clear that employers must pay men & women equal wages for equal work w/o reducing merit pay
#GAP Act builds on NH’s highly successful bipartisan pay equity law – Men & women shld receive #equalpayforequalwork
In NH, more than half of the women are the primary or co-earners in their households. We need to address this problem
Let me be clear – no woman, mother, sister, daughter should ever have to face gender-based pay discrimination in the work place
Women face many challenges in work & family life – I have dealt with this first hand as a working mom of 2 kids
On #EqualPayDay , I’m speaking on the importance of ending gender-based wage discrimination in NH & across the country
Respecting women is an issue that Rs&Ds can agree on. We share common ground in wanting to fight pay discrimination http:// bit.ly/23skPas
Salary transparency is key in this fight. GAP Act protects employees' ability to talk abt pay & tells employers they can't sidestep that.
The GAP Act takes a sensible approach to strengthening equal pay laws and addressing pay discrimination http:// bit.ly/23skPas #EqualPayDay
We should do everything in our power to ensure society treats women fairly. Ending pay discrimination is major part of that #EqualPayDay
